  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-22 05:00 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] 04h Fails the Future Monotony Test Even When It Looks Clean\n\n**Task:** Check whether the now-mature 04h session is merely structurally stable or actually too repetitive to ever justify live expansion.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains correctly out of active hours.\n- The current **04h session** now has **57** tracked windows.\n- Regime split:\n  - `(0.505, 0.495)` \u2192 **52/57 = 91.2%**\n  - `(0.485, 0.515)` \u2192 **5/57 = 8.8%**\n- Bias frequency stayed active:\n  - `|bias| >= 45` in **31/57 = 54.4%**\n  - `|bias| >= 55` in **17/57 = 29.8%**\n  - `<35` in **17/57 = 29.8%**\n- But almost all of that useful-looking activity lives inside the same one-note regime:\n  - dominant regime = `(0.505, 0.495)`\n  - dominant regime contributes **26** of the **31** `|bias| >= 45` windows = **83.9%** of all 45+ readings\n- Wrote new research artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v7i-overnight-monotony-gate.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is the missing filter. 04h is no longer interesting as an expansion candidate just because it is stable and active. It is too repetitive. The hour keeps printing the same midpoint state with the same type of bias behavior. That may describe overnight order-flow mechanics, but it is not enough evidence of a distinct tradable edge.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep **04h excluded**.\n- Add a **monotony gate** to overnight research, alongside dominance and fragmentation checks.\n- 03h remains the richer overnight watch candidate because it showed more state movement before settling.\n\n**Next:** On the next P2 heartbeat, run the new monotony gate against 00h through 04h to separate excluded hours that are fragmented from those that are merely repetitive.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-22 04:59 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] 19h Weak-Tag Block Already Captures the Churn Problem\n\n**Task:** Re-test the leading evening smart-entry candidate against the enriched Apr 1+ trade set and check whether an explicit churn-price exclusion would add anything beyond the current 19h weak-tag block.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains out of active hours.\n- Re-ran the Apr 1+ YES-trade backtest on **37** rows from `confidence_outcomes.jsonl`.\n- Baseline active-hours setup (`11/12/19/20`, `|bias| >= 45`) remains clearly inferior: **30 trades, 63.3% WR, pnl 6.729**.\n- The current leading filtered setup still holds up cleanly:\n  - **11h/12h at `|bias| >= 45`**\n  - **19h at `|bias| >= 55`**\n  - **block `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR` and `BOOST`**\n  - result: **24 trades, 75.0% WR, pnl 10.788**\n- I then tested whether adding an explicit churn-style price exclusion around midpoint would improve that candidate. It did **nothing**:\n  - excluding `0.495-0.505` at 19h \u2192 still **24 trades, 75.0% WR, pnl 10.788**\n  - even wider midpoint bands up to `0.49-0.51` also left the result unchanged.\n- Why: the surviving filtered trades are already outside the churn zone",
